    • Method Detail

      • getAppIdOrCategoryOrClazz

        public List<Object> getAppIdOrCategoryOrClazz()
        Gets the value of the appIdOrCategoryOrClazz property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the appIdOrCategoryOrClazz property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getAppIdOrCategoryOrClazz().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list IsolateComponent Category Registry CopyFile CreateFolder ProgId ODBCTranslator ServiceInstall AppId RemoveRegistryKey RegistryKey Environment Class File ODBCDriver SymbolPath ServiceConfigFailureActions Interface RegistryValue Element Shortcut ServiceControl IniFile Condition ServiceConfig RemoveFolder RemoveFile ReserveCost TypeLib RemoveRegistryValue Object Extension ODBCDataSource

      • getOtherAttributes

        public Map<QName,String> getOtherAttributes()
        Gets a map that contains attributes that aren't bound to any typed property on this class.

        the map is keyed by the name of the attribute and the value is the string value of the attribute. the map returned by this method is live, and you can add new attribute by updating the map directly. Because of this design, there's no setter.

        Returns:
        always non-null
